{\par \b Syntax:}\par gramschmidt(Basis(B),ScalarProd(Sp))\par
{\par \b Description:}\par Returns an orthonormal base of E of base B for the scalar product Sp.\par
{\par \b Example:}\par gramschmidt([1,1+x],(p,q)->integrate(p*q,x,-1,1)) returns [1/(\u8730?2),(1+x-1)/(\u8730?6)/3]\par }